
[1]fumigation

   FUMIGA'TION, n. [L. fumigatio.]

   1. The act of smoking or applying smoke, as in chimistry for softening
   a metal, or in the healing art by inhaling the smoke of certain
   substances. Expectoration is often assisted and sometimes ulcers of the
   lungs healed by fumigation. Fumigation is also used in cleansing
   infected rooms.

   2. Vapors; scent raised by fire.
